claim.claim-text:
1. A seating condition detecting system comprising: 
a right front load sensor for detecting a load to which a right front elastic body that supports a right front part of a seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left front load sensor for detecting load to which a left front elastic body that supports a left front part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a right rear load sensor for detecting load to which a right rear elastic body that supports a right rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left rear load sensor for detecting load to which a left rear elastic body that supports a left rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a seating condition detecting means for detecting a seating condition of a vehicle occupant based on the loads detected by the load sensors; 
a belt tension sensor for detecting tension of a seat belt that restrains the vehicle occupant or secures a child seat; and 
a self-diagnostic means for determining an abnormal operation when a total load detected by the load sensors falls into a first abnormal range that is set so that an upper limit of the range becomes higher as the belt tension becomes higher or within a second abnormal range that is set so that a lower limit of the range becomes higher as the belt tension deviates from the point at which the total load becomes lowest.

2. A seating condition detecting system comprising: 
a right front load sensor for detecting load to which a right front elastic body that supports a right front part of a seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left front load sensor for detecting load to which a left front elastic body that supports a left front part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a right rear load sensor for detecting load to which a right rear elastic body that supports a right rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left rear load sensor for detecting load to which a left rear elastic body that supports a left rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a seating condition detecting means for detecting a seating condition of a vehicle occupant based on the loads detected by the load sensors; and 
a self-diagnostic means for determining an abnormal operation when at least one of the loads detected by the load sensors has a negative value and its absolute value is heavier than a predetermined value.

3. A seating condition detecting system comprising: 
a right front load sensor for detecting load to which a right front elastic body that supports a right front part of a seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left front load sensor for detecting load to which a left front elastic body that supports a left front part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a right rear load sensor for detecting load to which a right rear elastic body that supports a right rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left rear load sensor for detecting load to which a left rear elastic body that supports a left rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a seating condition detecting means for detecting a seating condition of a vehicle occupant based on the loads detected by the load sensors; and 
a self-diagnostic means for determining an abnormal operation when differences between the right front load and left front load, and between the right rear load and left rear load, both indicating seating position of the vehicular occupant either rightward or leftward, contradict each other, or when differences between the right front load and right rear load, and between the left front load and left rear load, both indicating seating position of the vehicular occupant either forward or backward, contradict each other.

4. A seating condition detecting system comprising: 
an empty seat detecting sensor for detecting presence or absence of a vehicle occupant or a child seat; 
a belt tension sensor for detecting belt tension of a seat belt that restrains a seated vehicle occupant or secures the child seat; 
a right front load sensor for detecting load to which a right front elastic body that supports a right front part of a seat on which the child seat is mounted or the vehicle occupant is seated from underneath is subjected; 
a left front load sensor for detecting load to which a left front elastic body that supports a left front part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a right rear load sensor for detecting load to which a right rear elastic body that supports a right rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left rear load sensor for detecting load to which a left rear elastic body that supports a left rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; and 
a seating condition detecting means for detecting a seating condition of the vehicle occupant based on the loads detected by the load sensors; and 
a self-diagnostic means for determining an abnormal operation when at least one of the loads detected by the load sensors is heavier than a predetermined value although an empty seat is detected by the empty seat detecting sensor.

5. A seating condition detecting system comprising: 
an empty seat detecting sensor for detecting presence or absence of a vehicle occupant or a child seat; 
a belt tension sensor for detecting belt tension of a seat belt that restrains a seated vehicle occupant or secures the child seat; 
a right front load sensor for detecting load to which a right front elastic body that supports a right front part of a seat on which the child seat is mounted or the vehicle occupant is seated from underneath is subjected; 
a left front load sensor for detecting load to which a left front elastic body that supports a left front part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a right rear load sensor for detecting load to which a right rear elastic body that supports a right rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left rear load sensor for detecting load to which a left rear elastic body that supports a left rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; and 
a seating condition detecting means for detecting a seating condition of the vehicle occupant based on the loads detected by the load sensors; and 
a self-diagnostic means for determining an abnormal operation when the belt tension higher than a predetermined value is detected although an empty seat is detected by the empty seat detecting system.

6. A seating condition detecting system comprising: 
a right front load sensor for detecting load to which a right front elastic body that supports a right front part of a seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left front load sensor for detecting load to which a left front elastic body that supports a left front part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a right rear load sensor for detecting load to which a right rear elastic body that supports a right rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left rear load sensor for detecting load to which a left rear elastic body that supports a left rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; and 
a seating condition detecting means for detecting a seating condition of the vehicle occupant based on the loads detected by the load sensors; and 
a self-diagnostic means for determining an abnormal operation when any three of the four loads detected by the load sensors are equal to or lighter than a first threshold and the remaining load is heavier than a second threshold.

7. A seating condition detecting system comprising: 
a right front load sensor for detecting load to which a right front elastic body that supports a right front part of a seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left front load sensor for detecting load to which a left front elastic body that supports a left front part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a right rear load sensor for detecting load to which a right rear elastic body that supports a right rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; 
a left rear load sensor for detecting load to which a left rear elastic body that supports a left rear part of the seat from underneath is subjected; and 
a seating condition detecting means for detecting a seating condition of the vehicle occupant based on the loads detected by the load sensors; and 
a self-diagnostic means for determining an abnormal operation when any three of the four loads detected by the load sensors are equal to or heavier than a first threshold and the remaining load is lighter than a second threshold.
